          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780997663341" href="/book/show/58454052-why-they-stay">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4172699008" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13693034487462578010">Why They Stay: Sex Scandals, Deals, and Hidden Agendas of Eight Political Wives by Anne Michaud is a read that will open a world most of us only get a glimpse of through the papers. The glamour and prestige of marrying powerful and influential men of our country is a privilege and a potential time bomb many women are willing to accept. The habit of running a country or state comes with the knowledge that you often get what you want when you want it. But that doesn&apos;t fair well with a marriage. Th</span>
  <span id="freeText13693034487462578010" style="display:none">Why They Stay: Sex Scandals, Deals, and Hidden Agendas of Eight Political Wives by Anne Michaud is a read that will open a world most of us only get a glimpse of through the papers. The glamour and prestige of marrying powerful and influential men of our country is a privilege and a potential time bomb many women are willing to accept. The habit of running a country or state comes with the knowledge that you often get what you want when you want it. But that doesn't fair well with a marriage. The public expects men, and women, in leadership to be as faithful and loyal in their marriage as they are to serving the people. It is a flaw to be unfaithful in any area. The women who stand behind their husband's unfaithfulness are scrutinized as to why they would forgive or accept this action. This book speculates the motive behind the wives that stayed. It is an interesting read; some I disagreed with, but considering the evidence available, most rang true. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13693034487462578010" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


